    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "A bunch of properties in the codebase are defined using `property` without the decorator syntax, which, while valid, isn't very intuitive anymore.\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndef _get_some_value(self):\r\n    ...\r\n\r\ndef _set_some_value(self, value):\r\n    ...\r\n\r\nsome_value = property(_get_some_value, _set_some_value, doc=\"...\")\r\ndel _get_some_value, _set_some_value\r\n```\r\n\r\n```python\r\n@property\r\ndef some_value(self):\r\n    \"\"\"...\"\"\"\r\n    ...\r\n\r\n@some_value.setter\r\ndef some_value(self, value):\r\n    ...\r\n```",
